      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LEKTRA STING (1) hit the ground running from the squeeze draw with a fast early split last time, but run over late and missed the frame when a 1.3 lengths fourth (23.49) over 410m at this track. Has won two of two starts from this draw. Has ability and is a key runner. PAW RENALLA (2) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by 0.9 lengths at Ballarat in a handy 22.20. Has a low draw and has the ability and in winning form. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to her credit. In sparkling form and looks the one to beat again. LOUIE CABANG (7) comes off an average performance last start when fifth at Shepparton over 450m behind Paw Tarkov (25.74) in a Grade 5. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Must be included in calculations. SMOOTH COLLINDA (8) gets a chance to redeem an unplaced effort here last start.",
